aVHow does evolution do cumulative, combinatorial things?
p85
aVWell, it uses sexual reproduction.
p86
aVIn an asexual species, if you get two different mutations in different creatures,
p87
aVa green one and a red one,
p88
aVthen one has to be better than the other.
p89
aVOne goes extinct for the other to survive.
p90
aVBut if you have a sexual species,
p91
aVthen it's possible for an individual
p92
aVto inherit both mutations
p93
aVfrom different lineages.
p94
aVSo what sex does is it enables the individual
p95
aVto draw upon
p96
aVthe genetic innovations of the whole species.
p97
aVIt's not confined to its own lineage.
