p115
aVThey teach each other traditions
p116
aVwhich are handed down from parent to offspring.
p117
aVIn this case, chimpanzees teaching each other
p118
aVhow to crack nuts with rocks.
p119
aVBut the difference is
p120
aVthat these cultures never expand, never grow,
p121
aVnever accumulate, never become combinatorial,
p122
aVand the reason is because
p123
aVthere is no sex, as it were,
p124
aVthere is no exchange of ideas.
p125
aVChimpanzee troops have different cultures in different troops.
p126
aVThere's no exchange of ideas between them.
